  "text": "Measurements were made in a 10-year-old shrubland at the Yanchi Research Station (37˝42 1 31\"N, 107˝13 [CITATION_1] 45\"E, 1530 m above sea level (a.s.l.)), Ningxia, Northwest China. The research site is located at the southern edge of the Mu Us desert and is characterized by a mid-temperate semiarid continental monsoon climate. The site is dominated by a mixture of deciduous shrub species including Artemisia ordosica, Hedysarum mongolicum, Hedysarum scoparium and sparsely distributed Agropyron cristatum. The canopy height was about 1.4 m and the maximum Leaf Area Index (LAI) was 1.20 m 2¨m´2 during the study period.",
